Decided architecture (v0.2, 2026-04-12):
- Language: Python, SDK via ctypes, models via onnxruntime-gpu
- Video: RTSP + OpenCV (not SDK preview callback)
- 3 preset positions covering full space, software-controlled patrol (not SDK cruise)
- State machine: PATROL (idle cycling) ↔ SCAN (per-preset face detection + zoom + recognize)
- ReID: OSNet_x0_25 for cross-preset de-duplication
- Person detection: YOLOv8n COCO (allowed by user)
- Face detection: YOLO11n-face (640 for close, 1280 for wide) — NMS not built-in, must post-process
- Face recognition: ArcFace 112×112 → 512-d, no landmark alignment for now
- Recording: on-demand via NET_DVR_StartDVRRecord, keyboard toggle 'v'

**Why:** Python chosen for demo speed; RTSP chosen for simplicity over SDK callbacks; 3 presets because 2x zoom is too limited for single-position coverage.

**How to apply:** Implementation follows 8 milestones (M1-M8) defined in 详细设计书.md §10.
